1
00:00:36,494 --> 00:00:37,620
Bok!

2
00:00:40,457 --> 00:00:42,542
What's this? Did you kidnap her?

3
00:00:43,418 --> 00:00:44,419
She attacked me last night.

4
00:00:50,049 --> 00:00:51,676
Someone has to do it, Bok.

5
00:00:52,677 --> 00:00:53,511
<i>Is it why Carlota's here?</i>

6
00:00:53,595 --> 00:00:55,889
<i>It's because you want</i>
<i>somebody to watch over me?</i>

7
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:02,812
Why did you release her?

8
00:01:04,939 --> 00:01:07,108
You let go of La Fornarina.

9
00:01:07,692 --> 00:01:09,527
She is not La Fornarina.

10
00:01:09,611 --> 00:01:10,987
La Fornarina is left-handed.

11
00:01:22,791 --> 00:01:25,627
<i>These drivers are always</i>
<i>delayed in deliveries.</i>

12
00:01:25,710 --> 00:01:27,629
There is no sign of reprimand.

13
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:31,883
Why is that?

14
00:01:32,801 --> 00:01:34,928
<i>I need to report this to Agent Alex.</i>

15
00:01:49,234 --> 00:01:55,156
<i>They said I shouldn't use this phone.</i>
<i>I need to listen to Agent Alex.</i>

16
00:02:05,917 --> 00:02:08,253
You really love leading people on, Mikoy.

17
00:02:08,336 --> 00:02:10,046
Such a heartbreaker.

18
00:02:30,191 --> 00:02:32,944
Who was the one you sent that messed up?

19
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:37,031
Chihuahua.

20
00:02:43,371 --> 00:02:45,415
and now he is even more exposed.

21
00:02:49,085 --> 00:02:51,629
And maybe you're forgetting something.

22
00:02:54,632 --> 00:02:56,134
Norberto.

23
00:02:56,217 --> 00:02:57,635
For La Morte Bianca.

24
00:02:58,261 --> 00:02:59,971
So you focus on that

25
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:01,848
and let me handle this.

26
00:03:08,563 --> 00:03:09,856
What's the agent's name?

27
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:31,669
I'll play your game,

28
00:03:31,753 --> 00:03:35,006
but as soon as I finish with my mission,

29
00:03:35,089 --> 00:03:37,091
you will give me all the information

30
00:03:37,175 --> 00:03:39,552
about the agent getting close to Mikoy,

31
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:42,305
and I'll deal with that bastard next.

32
00:03:58,029 --> 00:03:59,447
Are you sure you're okay?

33
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:02,742
Yes, sir, I'm fine.

34
00:04:02,825 --> 00:04:03,785
Just a stomach bug.

35
00:04:04,452 --> 00:04:07,497
Good thing Agent Sianong was there.
He always carries medicine.

36
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:11,376
Sir, we have a problem.

37
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:14,128
The sensors at the back were triggered!

38
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:15,922
Someone's breaking into the secret door!

39
00:04:17,006 --> 00:04:18,424
Kian, secure General Norberto.

40
00:04:18,508 --> 00:04:19,342
Let's go, sir.

41
00:04:19,425 --> 00:04:20,468
Hold on a second!

42
00:04:20,551 --> 00:04:21,469
Stop it!

43
00:04:22,136 --> 00:04:24,597
Who do you think I am?
A civilian who needs protection?

44
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:26,099
I can fight.

45
00:04:35,483 --> 00:04:37,026
Team, let's go.

46
00:04:44,909 --> 00:04:46,077
Go.

47
00:04:55,712 --> 00:04:57,505
Hands up! Or we'll shoot--

48
00:05:00,758 --> 00:05:01,801
Mikoy?

49
00:05:03,928 --> 00:05:04,929
Hmm?

50
00:05:10,226 --> 00:05:13,229
Really? Laurence is your date
for the concert?

51
00:05:13,813 --> 00:05:15,023
Why? Is that bad?

52
00:05:16,232 --> 00:05:19,235
No, I am just surprised.

53
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:21,779
Luisa Mae said

54
00:05:21,863 --> 00:05:23,364
that you were coming with us.

55
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:25,450
She also said that

56
00:05:26,826 --> 00:05:29,787
you were bringing your boyfriend, so…

57
00:05:29,871 --> 00:05:30,872
You mean,

58
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:33,416
you and Laurence are…?

59
00:05:33,499 --> 00:05:34,334
Okay.

60
00:05:34,417 --> 00:05:35,752
Let's just say that

61
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:38,629
we're still in the getting-to-know stage.

62
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:40,798
But there's no label yet.

63
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:44,886
Oh, right.

64
00:05:44,969 --> 00:05:47,346
You're not really into labels.

65
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,182
Why? Is that bad?

66
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:51,225
No.

67
00:05:51,309 --> 00:05:53,352
I did not mean to insult you.

68
00:05:53,436 --> 00:05:55,980
You didn't mean to, but you already did.

69
00:05:56,064 --> 00:05:57,607
I'm sorry.

70
00:05:57,690 --> 00:05:59,442
Okay, how about this?

71
00:06:00,109 --> 00:06:01,569
Once we get to the concert,

72
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:03,905
I'll give you and Laurence some space

73
00:06:03,988 --> 00:06:07,075
so the two of you can
get closer to each other.

74
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:09,786
And…

75
00:06:10,703 --> 00:06:15,083
I'm also planning to propose to Luisa Mae.

76
00:06:16,918 --> 00:06:18,211
Propose what?

77
00:06:18,294 --> 00:06:19,629
Propose!

78
00:06:20,129 --> 00:06:21,464
To formalize our relationship!

79
00:06:21,547 --> 00:06:23,966
So we can officially
become boyfriend and girlfriend.

80
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:25,051
So finally,

81
00:06:25,134 --> 00:06:26,928
we'll have a label for each other.

82
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:28,846
Right?

83
00:06:41,984 --> 00:06:43,152
Lower your gun.

84
00:06:47,323 --> 00:06:48,908
Sianong, lower your gun.

85
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:51,327
You first.

86
00:06:58,835 --> 00:07:00,378
What are you doing, huh?

87
00:07:00,962 --> 00:07:03,339
Do you even know
you almost got yourself shot?

88
00:07:03,422 --> 00:07:06,384
And what are you doing
at our secret door, like an agent?

89
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:07,635
How did you know about that?

90
00:07:10,638 --> 00:07:12,432
I'm the one who told him about it.

91
00:07:13,224 --> 00:07:14,892
I told him to use that entrance,

92
00:07:14,976 --> 00:07:18,062
so our enemies wouldn't discover
the identity of our secret asset.

93
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:22,525
That's it, just like what Alex said.

94
00:07:22,608 --> 00:07:24,402
Secret door for the…

95
00:07:24,485 --> 00:07:25,903
secret asset.

96
00:07:26,863 --> 00:07:29,031
But, Mikoy, what are you doing here?

97
00:07:29,532 --> 00:07:33,286
I specifically instructed you
to wait for our instructions,

98
00:07:33,369 --> 00:07:35,371
to wait for us to contact you.

99
00:07:35,913 --> 00:07:37,874
Didn't you understand what I said?

100
00:08:01,355 --> 00:08:02,607
Because I missed you.

101
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:04,775
Okay?

102
00:08:13,117 --> 00:08:14,452
I miss your eyes…

103
00:08:17,705 --> 00:08:18,915
your voice…

104
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:23,127
your touch,

105
00:08:25,254 --> 00:08:26,297
everything.

106
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:29,550
I really missed you.

107
00:08:44,565 --> 00:08:45,691
Why?

108
00:08:48,152 --> 00:08:50,321
Do you feel the same way about me?

109
00:09:04,001 --> 00:09:06,128
Just kidding! Come on!

110
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:07,421
Are you okay?

111
00:09:07,505 --> 00:09:09,006
You're way too tense.

112
00:09:10,132 --> 00:09:12,593
Loosen up a little. Come on.

113
00:09:12,677 --> 00:09:14,637
You know, you had too much coffee.

114
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:17,181
One day, I'm really gonna get you.

115
00:09:17,848 --> 00:09:20,309
Come on. I was kidding.
You can't even take a joke.

116
00:09:20,393 --> 00:09:22,144
I really did miss you, guys.

117
00:09:23,062 --> 00:09:24,855
What are you even doing here?

118
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:30,361
I'm here because I have
new information you need to know.

119
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:40,663
So tasty!

120
00:09:41,205 --> 00:09:42,373
Thank you.

121
00:09:43,332 --> 00:09:46,127
By the way, why were you all
so worked up earlier?

122
00:09:46,711 --> 00:09:48,129
You had too much coffee, didn't you?

123
00:09:48,212 --> 00:09:49,922
That's why you don't want coffee now?

124
00:09:55,177 --> 00:09:58,139
And we think the Moravianos
are trying to kill our agency director.

125
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:02,268
Sir… Norberto Ruiz?

126
00:10:02,351 --> 00:10:03,686
Yes.

127
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:06,522
A lot has happened these past few days,

128
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:09,275
and the Moravianos
already know everything we're doing.

129
00:10:09,358 --> 00:10:12,278
And another thing.
We're already on their radar.

130
00:10:12,361 --> 00:10:16,240
They even sent La Fornarina
just to silence Alex.

131
00:10:20,828 --> 00:10:22,038
It's nothing.

132
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:24,749
No, it's not.

133
00:10:24,832 --> 00:10:26,167
It's not just nothing.

134
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:28,127
Are you okay?

135
00:10:29,128 --> 00:10:30,755
I'm fine.

136
00:10:30,838 --> 00:10:32,506
I'm a special agent.

137
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:33,924
I can handle it. You know me.

138
00:10:34,008 --> 00:10:35,760
Even if you can handle it,
even if you're used to it,

139
00:10:35,843 --> 00:10:37,511
it still affects you, right?

140
00:10:37,595 --> 00:10:39,639
Maybe not physically,

141
00:10:39,722 --> 00:10:40,765
but spiritually,

142
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:42,391
mentally,

143
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:43,517
emotionally.

144
00:10:44,935 --> 00:10:46,771
- Mikoy.
- Alex!

145
00:10:47,355 --> 00:10:48,898
Look at me.

146
00:10:50,191 --> 00:10:51,484
I want to know.

147
00:10:53,402 --> 00:10:55,029
Are you really okay?

148
00:10:56,739 --> 00:10:58,449
What is the meaning of this?

149
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:00,826
Oh…

150
00:11:01,535 --> 00:11:02,995
Who is this new face?

151
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:08,459
Who is this?

152
00:11:09,293 --> 00:11:10,461
Your new boyfriend?

153
00:11:11,462 --> 00:11:13,798
Another pretty boy actor wannabe.

154
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:18,886
Is he a new member of <i>Starworx of Mr. M</i>?

155
00:11:20,638 --> 00:11:22,431
What if I really am her boyfriend?

156
00:11:23,808 --> 00:11:24,642
Why?

157
00:11:25,142 --> 00:11:26,268
Got a problem with that?

158
00:11:29,063 --> 00:11:30,731
See?

159
00:11:30,815 --> 00:11:33,025
We're not human. We're not animals.

160
00:11:33,692 --> 00:11:34,860
We're a thing.

161
00:11:37,863 --> 00:11:42,493
Bro! Is it true that you and Sofie…

162
00:11:43,619 --> 00:11:45,329
Why? Is it that unbelievable?

163
00:11:46,747 --> 00:11:48,541
Not really.

164
00:11:48,624 --> 00:11:52,336
I just thought you weren't Sofie's type.

165
00:11:53,421 --> 00:11:56,006
Maybe I just misunderstood her.

166
00:11:56,632 --> 00:11:58,300
If you know her that well,

167
00:11:58,384 --> 00:11:59,552
do you know,

168
00:12:00,052 --> 00:12:01,095
or did you at least ask,

169
00:12:01,178 --> 00:12:02,972
what she thinks about Luisa Mae?

170
00:12:03,055 --> 00:12:05,182
Did you ask her permission
about Luisa Mae?

171
00:12:05,266 --> 00:12:06,350
Permission?

172
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:08,436
Why would I ask permission?

173
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:11,397
She already knows
how much I like Luisa Mae.

174
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:14,316
She was actually the first one
who became friends with Luisa.

175
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,277
And after that,

176
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:18,237
Luisa and I started talking.

177
00:12:19,655 --> 00:12:21,699
Wait, why are you asking anyway?

178
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:25,077
Oh, Angelito!

179
00:12:25,161 --> 00:12:27,455
That sigh was a bit too much, bro.

180
00:12:28,164 --> 00:12:31,250
Have you heard about the theory of us men

181
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:33,752
who tend to develop emotionally
a bit later?

182
00:12:33,836 --> 00:12:35,212
Meaning, we mature late.

183
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:37,214
You mean,

184
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:39,884
we're late bloomers?

185
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:41,302
Exactly.

186
00:12:41,385 --> 00:12:44,221
We're late bloomers
when it comes to relationships.

187
00:12:45,347 --> 00:12:47,016
I don't believe that, bro.

188
00:12:47,099 --> 00:12:48,267
Come on. Tell me.

189
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:50,144
You already had a girlfriend in Grade 5.

190
00:12:50,227 --> 00:12:52,771
We're quick when it comes to girlfriends,

191
00:12:52,855 --> 00:12:56,317
but it doesn't mean we're already
mature enough for relationships.

192
00:12:57,318 --> 00:12:58,277
Wait.

193
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:02,072
What's this philosophical discourse for?

194
00:13:04,575 --> 00:13:06,035
So you really don't get it?

195
00:13:07,786 --> 00:13:10,122
You know the snake's about to bite you.

196
00:13:10,664 --> 00:13:12,374
It's so obvious.

197
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:13,709
It's right in front of you.

198
00:13:15,211 --> 00:13:16,086
Huh?

199
00:13:17,671 --> 00:13:19,173
You know what? Whatever.

200
00:13:19,256 --> 00:13:20,633
I'm heading inside.

201
00:13:20,716 --> 00:13:21,884
Take care.

202
00:13:28,682 --> 00:13:30,476
We do have a love team, right?

203
00:13:33,145 --> 00:13:34,230
MikLex.

204
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:36,524
Mikoy and Alex.

205
00:13:38,859 --> 00:13:40,611
MikLex, my ass.

206
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:42,321
So corny!

207
00:13:42,404 --> 00:13:46,367
You and Lai… still look better together.

208
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:47,284
- Lai?
- Lai…

209
00:13:47,368 --> 00:13:48,577
Laida Magtalas.

210
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:50,871
But wait.

211
00:13:51,705 --> 00:13:53,582
You do look familiar.

212
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:55,251
I think I've seen you before.

213
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:56,627
Well…

214
00:13:58,003 --> 00:14:01,048
as the Bisdak Heartthrob of Cebu City,

215
00:14:01,131 --> 00:14:03,259
people really have mistaken me
for an actor before.

216
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:05,761
Sometimes even the King of Gil,
who's haggard.

217
00:14:05,844 --> 00:14:07,388
I got it!

218
00:14:07,471 --> 00:14:10,224
You look exactly like this idiot I know,

219
00:14:10,307 --> 00:14:12,601
Gabo Villarica.

220
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:16,146
The one who ghosted
my friend Belinda Dimagiba.

221
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:17,356
Huh?

222
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:19,275
Where did that come from?

223
00:14:19,358 --> 00:14:20,317
From me!

224
00:14:20,401 --> 00:14:21,360
Are you deaf?

225
00:14:21,443 --> 00:14:23,779
Oh, no, Alex,
you better be careful with him.

226
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:25,239
You're both ghosts.

227
00:14:25,322 --> 00:14:27,324
He might leave you too
without saying goodbye.

228
00:14:27,408 --> 00:14:28,784
Just like what you did to me.

229
00:14:29,785 --> 00:14:30,911
That's enough.

230
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:34,164
It's Mikoy.

231
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:36,667
You saw him at the hospital.

232
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:38,711
The one who got shot
at the Valtrovi event.

233
00:14:39,503 --> 00:14:41,005
He's working for us.

234
00:14:41,088 --> 00:14:42,172
He's our asset.

235
00:14:43,173 --> 00:14:44,425
I know.

236
00:14:44,508 --> 00:14:45,968
I was just messing with him.

237
00:14:46,552 --> 00:14:48,178
But this is a surprise, huh?

238
00:14:48,846 --> 00:14:51,974
Who would've thought
the dumb victim from the Valtrovi event

239
00:14:52,057 --> 00:14:54,852
is actually the asset of this agency?

240
00:14:54,935 --> 00:14:56,395
Hey, watch it!

241
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:57,855
Don't judge me. I'm not a book.

242
00:14:57,938 --> 00:14:59,815
And wow, thanks for calling me dumb.

243
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:02,318
Why? Can't you take a bullet
for the one you love?

244
00:15:06,405 --> 00:15:09,950
I'm just saying that
if you are an important asset,

245
00:15:10,034 --> 00:15:13,037
you should learn how to protect yourself

246
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,788
to not get shot.

247
00:15:14,872 --> 00:15:16,790
I already know how! I've been training!

248
00:15:16,874 --> 00:15:18,417
You wanna go 1-on-1?

249
00:15:19,126 --> 00:15:20,336
Enough already.

250
00:15:21,086 --> 00:15:23,172
Mikoy, tell us about
the fresh information you mentioned.

251
00:15:23,255 --> 00:15:24,089
That's why you're here.

252
00:15:24,173 --> 00:15:25,174
Oh, right!

253
00:15:25,257 --> 00:15:26,634
You distracted me with coffee,

254
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:28,344
and this guy's being extra.

255
00:15:28,427 --> 00:15:29,845
I almost forgot.

256
00:15:30,721 --> 00:15:32,514
Anyway, I'm here

257
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:34,725
because I brought fresh information.

258
00:15:35,976 --> 00:15:38,812
But I have even fresher information.

259
00:15:39,563 --> 00:15:40,689
Did you know

260
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:44,735
that some turtles
can breathe through their butts?

261
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:47,571
Really, Ben?

262
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:50,032
You know, this is why you're always…

263
00:15:50,115 --> 00:15:51,241
no, not just always…

264
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:54,411
You're constantly out of pocket!

265
00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:55,704
Can you read the room?

266
00:15:56,205 --> 00:15:57,831
That's why you often get ghosted.

267
00:15:58,415 --> 00:15:59,667
Is that victim blaming?

268
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:01,210
Are you spying on turtles now?

269
00:16:01,293 --> 00:16:03,003
Stop it! Wait a minute!

270
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:06,966
I might forget
the fresh information again.

271
00:16:07,049 --> 00:16:07,967
Anyway…

272
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:11,971
There. You see that?

273
00:16:12,888 --> 00:16:17,810
These are all the files
of Vertex's drivers.

274
00:16:21,021 --> 00:16:21,855
Nice.

275
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:22,856
Anyway,

276
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:25,192
I'm here because I want to say

277
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:28,529
I think I've cracked down
on the Moravianos' local operation.

278
00:16:29,196 --> 00:16:31,824
I think I know how to bring them down.

279
00:16:32,408 --> 00:16:34,743
I noticed that there
are four Vertex drivers

280
00:16:34,827 --> 00:16:37,079
who are always late
for their delivery schedules at the port.

281
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:39,123
Every M, W, F.

282
00:16:39,206 --> 00:16:40,040
Over and over again.

283
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:41,625
And these drivers,

284
00:16:41,709 --> 00:16:43,419
not a single one has a report with HR.

285
00:16:43,502 --> 00:16:45,754
No suspension, no penalty.

286
00:16:45,838 --> 00:16:47,589
Looks like they have strong connections.

287
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:50,551
Not just strong connections.

288
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:53,178
More like a direct line to heaven.

289
00:16:58,267 --> 00:16:59,351
Something fishy.

290
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:06,650
But I think this is the breakthrough
that we need for this case.

291
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:08,569
Good job.

292
00:17:09,653 --> 00:17:10,904
You're right, Sianong.

293
00:17:11,822 --> 00:17:13,407
Thank you, Mikoy, for the intel.

294
00:17:24,126 --> 00:17:25,335
Who would've thought?

295
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:36,722
Peace offering.

296
00:17:36,805 --> 00:17:38,140
One for each of us.

297
00:17:38,223 --> 00:17:41,435
Yes, Angelito and I are cool now!

298
00:17:47,357 --> 00:17:49,026
<i>If you know her that well,</i>

299
00:17:49,109 --> 00:17:50,110
<i>do you know,</i>

300
00:17:50,819 --> 00:17:51,820
<i>or did you at least ask,</i>

301
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:53,697
<i>what's her opinion about Luisa Mae?</i>

302
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:55,949
<i>Did you ask permission about Luisa Mae?</i>

303
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:09,630
<i>Why isn't Sofie replying?</i>
<i>Sofie, please answer me.</i>

304
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:23,018
Hey, you called?

305
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:27,648
Well, I just thought about Sofie.

306
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:29,608
Are you still together?

307
00:18:29,691 --> 00:18:32,402
Didn't you have
the same last subject earlier?

308
00:18:32,486 --> 00:18:35,906
Yes, but after class,
I went to the library.

309
00:18:37,032 --> 00:18:39,284
So you're still at the library now?

310
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:41,912
No, I had somewhere to go.

311
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,623
Why? Why are you looking for her?

312
00:18:48,502 --> 00:18:49,795
<i>Um…</i>

313
00:18:49,878 --> 00:18:51,547
<i>I wanted to ask her out to eat.</i>

314
00:18:51,630 --> 00:18:55,008
She usually gets night cravings
around this time.

315
00:18:56,093 --> 00:18:57,344
But all right.

316
00:18:57,427 --> 00:19:00,347
Bro, if you see her, just tell her

317
00:19:00,430 --> 00:19:02,057
that my room's open for hangout again.

318
00:19:04,184 --> 00:19:06,645
I don't think
we'll be seeing each other, bro.

319
00:19:06,728 --> 00:19:08,063
Because earlier,

320
00:19:08,147 --> 00:19:11,525
when class ended, she left in a hurry.

321
00:19:11,608 --> 00:19:14,069
So maybe she's getting her beauty rest.

322
00:19:16,864 --> 00:19:19,366
Yes, that makes sense.

323
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:21,201
Why?

324
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:23,412
Do you miss her?

325
00:19:25,914 --> 00:19:27,040
<i>Yes.</i>

326
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:30,836
I kinda miss that idiot annoying me.

327
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:33,046
She was always bothering me.

328
00:19:34,047 --> 00:19:36,842
<i>So now I can really feel</i>

329
00:19:36,925 --> 00:19:38,927
<i>that her presence is missing.</i>

330
00:19:41,054 --> 00:19:42,431
But all right, bro, thanks.

331
00:19:43,390 --> 00:19:44,892
All right, bye.

332
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:55,777
Just hearing that someone misses you,

333
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:56,904
and you're already giggling.

334
00:19:59,239 --> 00:20:01,158
I'm not giggling, okay?

335
00:20:02,159 --> 00:20:03,827
Yes, that's true.

336
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:05,537
If you're just friends,

337
00:20:06,747 --> 00:20:08,123
then why are you avoiding him?

338
00:20:09,166 --> 00:20:10,626
You like him, don't you?

339
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:13,212
Or is it one-sided love?

340
00:20:17,925 --> 00:20:19,384
And you know what?

341
00:20:19,468 --> 00:20:22,638
A one-sided crush is better anyway.

342
00:20:22,721 --> 00:20:24,598
So why are you avoiding him?

343
00:20:25,515 --> 00:20:27,601
Because I can't take it anymore!

344
00:20:28,393 --> 00:20:31,396
It's always Luisa, Luisa, Luisa!

345
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:34,650
You know, when I sleep,
I even dream about Luisa now.

346
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:37,527
I know so much about Luisa already,

347
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:39,655
it feels like I'm the one who likes her

348
00:20:39,738 --> 00:20:41,531
because of your friend's stories.

349
00:20:42,157 --> 00:20:43,450
So that's it then?

350
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,245
You're giving up?

351
00:20:46,328 --> 00:20:48,247
Just because he's talking about Luisa Mae?

352
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:52,000
Maybe.

353
00:20:53,210 --> 00:20:54,920
How can you give up so easily

354
00:20:55,003 --> 00:20:57,256
when the fight hasn't even started yet?

355
00:20:57,339 --> 00:20:58,840
But haven't I already lost?

356
00:20:58,924 --> 00:21:01,051
Angelito likes Luisa.

357
00:21:02,386 --> 00:21:05,055
Don't give up just because
he likes someone else.

358
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:07,557
Be honest with your intentions

359
00:21:07,641 --> 00:21:08,976
and let him know

360
00:21:09,059 --> 00:21:11,270
that you and your feelings exist.

361
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:13,939
Fight for your feelings.

362
00:21:15,148 --> 00:21:16,400
You know what? You're right.

363
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:19,319
The fight is just getting started.

364
00:21:21,488 --> 00:21:22,781
I can do this.

365
00:21:28,078 --> 00:21:29,413
Are you okay?

366
00:21:29,496 --> 00:21:31,748
Well, I'm still alive.

367
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:35,127
I just need to get out of here.

368
00:21:35,210 --> 00:21:36,295
I can't go to the hospital.

369
00:21:36,378 --> 00:21:38,714
- Come on. Come with me.
- People will notice.

370
00:22:09,995 --> 00:22:11,496
Son of a…

371
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:12,873
You're still alive?

372
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:43,779
They say…

373
00:22:45,781 --> 00:22:47,282
I'm like a cat.

374
00:22:50,285 --> 00:22:51,703
I have nine lives.

375
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:14,267
Sweetheart?

376
00:23:17,354 --> 00:23:18,563
Are you there?

377
00:23:22,359 --> 00:23:23,568
Sweetheart.

378
00:23:25,362 --> 00:23:26,404
Are you there?

379
00:24:16,371 --> 00:24:18,665
And why should I trust you?

380
00:24:19,249 --> 00:24:22,419
I don't need your trust.
All you have to do is listen.
